Interface IEventArgs

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BendEventArgs, CanvasEvent, ClickEventArgs, CollectGraphSnapLinesEventArgs, CollectLabelSnapLineEventArgs, CollectSnapResultsEventArgs, CompoundKeyEvent, EdgeEventArgs, HandleDeserializationEventArgs, HandleSerializationEventArgs, HoveredItemChangedEventArgs, InputModeEventArgs, ItemChangedEventArgs, ItemClickedEventArgs, ItemCopiedEventArgs, ItemEventArgs, ItemSelectionChangedEventArgs, KeyEventArgs, LabelEditingEventArgs, LabelEventArgs, LabelTextValidatingEventArgs, LayoutEventArgs, MarqueeSelectionEventArgs, Mouse2DEvent, NodeEventArgs, ParseEventArgs, PopulateItemContextMenuEventArgs, PopulateMenuEventArgs, PortEventArgs, PrepareRenderContextEventArgs, PrintingEvent, PropertyChangedEventArgs, QueryInputHandlersEventArgs, QueryItemToolTipEventArgs, QueryOutputHandlersEventArgs, QueryPositionHandlerEventArgs, QueryReferenceIdEventArgs, RenderContextEvent, ResolveReferenceEventArgs, RoutedEventArgs, SelectionEventArgs, StripeEventArgs, TapEventArgs, TextEventArgs, ToolTipQueryEventArgs, Touch2DEvent, WriteEventArgs

    public interface IEventArgs
    EventArgs are part of the yFiles internal event handling infrastructure and contain values describing the event and the necessary information to process them.

    They are used by and tightly linked to yFiles IEventHandler.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static IEventArgs EMPTY
      EventArgs that contain no data.

    • Field Detail

      • EMPTY

        static final IEventArgs EMPTY
        EventArgs that contain no data. Useful in situations where to sole occurrence of an event is enough to successfully process the event.
